      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "906c516775bec27b",
      "text": "This, of course, would destroy the presupposition of a \"hierarchical opposition\" in the sense of an inherent or \"natural\" primacy of heterosexuality. At least we would see, if not effectively destroy, what [[Louis Dumont]] would call l'englobement du contraire – that is, the inclusion of oppositions into a hierarchical structure of preferred life-styles."
    },
